<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>According to standard HTTP/1.1 all transfer-coding values are case insensitive (<a href="http://www.w3.org/Protocols/HTTP/1.1/rfc2616bis/draft-lafon-rfc2616bis-03.html#transfer.codings">http://w3.org/Protocols/HTTP/â€¦</a>). But Zend_Http_Client_Adapter_Socket doesn't understand "{{Chunked}}" with first uppercased letter.</p>

<p>In the class there is simple compare {{$headers['transfer-encoding'] == 'chunked'}} (in method {{read()}}) without any respect to case insensitivity.</p>

